00:27:25,220 --> 00:27:27,220
to design its own software.

536
00:27:27,220 --> 00:27:29,220
The way they wanted,

537
00:27:29,220 --> 00:27:31,220
completely without Zangemann.

538
00:27:31,220 --> 00:27:32,220
Immediately,

539
00:27:32,220 --> 00:27:35,220
the president called his advisors.

540
00:27:35,220 --> 00:27:36,220
In a large group,

541
00:27:36,220 --> 00:27:38,220
they discussed with the children

542
00:27:38,220 --> 00:27:40,220
everything they could change

543
00:27:40,220 --> 00:27:42,220
and improve in the software.

544
00:27:42,220 --> 00:27:43,220
That evening,

545
00:27:43,220 --> 00:27:44,220
the children went home

546
00:27:44,220 --> 00:27:47,220
proud and satisfied.

547
00:27:47,220 --> 00:27:50,220
Something finally happened.

548
00:27:50,220 --> 00:27:51,220
Their long protest

549
00:27:51,220 --> 00:27:54,220
had been worth it.

550
00:27:54,220 --> 00:27:55,220
The next morning,

551
00:27:55,220 --> 00:27:56,220
the president's phone rang

552
00:27:56,220 --> 00:27:59,220
very early.

553
00:27:59,220 --> 00:28:01,220
It was Zangemann.

554
00:28:01,220 --> 00:28:05,220
He was angrier than ever.

555
00:28:05,220 --> 00:28:07,220
"Without me,

556
00:28:07,220 --> 00:28:08,220
the government computers

557
00:28:08,220 --> 00:28:10,220
will no longer work,"

558
00:28:10,220 --> 00:28:12,220
he threatened.

559
00:28:12,220 --> 00:28:13,220
But the president

560
00:28:13,220 --> 00:28:14,220
kept the call short

561
00:28:14,220 --> 00:28:17,220
and quickly hung up.

562
00:28:17,220 --> 00:28:18,220
The phone rang

563
00:28:18,220 --> 00:28:20,220
many more times that day,

564
00:28:20,220 --> 00:28:21,220
but Zangemann's calls

565
00:28:21,220 --> 00:28:23,220
went unanswered.

566
00:28:23,220 --> 00:28:24,220
The president sat in a meeting

567
00:28:24,220 --> 00:28:25,220
with Ada,

568
00:28:25,220 --> 00:28:27,220
Toni, Marie, Konrad,

569
00:28:27,220 --> 00:28:31,220
and the government experts.

570
00:28:31,220 --> 00:28:33,220
In the days that followed,

571
00:28:33,220 --> 00:28:35,220
they talked from morning to night

572
00:28:35,220 --> 00:28:36,220
and designed their first programs

573
00:28:36,220 --> 00:28:40,220
for the government's computers.

574
00:28:40,220 --> 00:28:42,220
They were no longer disturbed

575
00:28:42,220 --> 00:28:44,220
by Zangemann's calls.

576
00:28:44,220 --> 00:28:46,220
Toni had the good idea

577
00:28:46,220 --> 00:28:49,220
of reprogramming the telephones.

578
00:28:49,220 --> 00:28:50,220
When Zangemann called,

579
00:28:50,220 --> 00:28:51,220
he only heard

580
00:28:51,220 --> 00:28:54,220
an automated recording.

581
00:28:54,220 --> 00:28:56,220
The government only wants

582
00:28:56,220 --> 00:28:57,220
to use software

583
00:28:57,220 --> 00:28:59,220
that it can freely use,

584
00:28:59,220 --> 00:29:00,220
study,

585
00:29:00,220 --> 00:29:01,220
share,

586
00:29:01,220 --> 00:29:02,220
and improve.

587
00:29:02,220 --> 00:29:06,220
Thank you for calling.

588
00:29:06,220 --> 00:29:07,220
Then, after many weeks

589
00:29:07,220 --> 00:29:09,220
of protests and discussions,

590
00:29:09,220 --> 00:29:11,220
the time had finally come.

591
00:29:11,220 --> 00:29:12,220
They abolished

592
00:29:12,220 --> 00:29:13,220
the old Zangemann law.

593
00:29:13,220 --> 00:29:14,220
Instead,

594
00:29:14,220 --> 00:29:16,220
the government announced,

595
00:29:16,220 --> 00:29:17,220
"Everyone is allowed

596
00:29:17,220 --> 00:29:18,220
to program

597
00:29:18,220 --> 00:29:20,220
their own computers

598
00:29:20,220 --> 00:29:21,220
as long as they adhere

599
00:29:21,220 --> 00:29:23,220
to the other laws."

600
00:29:23,220 --> 00:29:24,220
In addition,

601
00:29:24,220 --> 00:29:25,220
a new school subject

602
00:29:25,220 --> 00:29:27,220
was introduced:

603
00:29:27,220 --> 00:29:28,220
computer hardware

604
00:29:28,220 --> 00:29:30,220
and software.

605
00:29:30,220 --> 00:29:32,220
That evening,

606
00:29:32,220 --> 00:29:33,220
everyone celebrated

607
00:29:33,220 --> 00:29:35,220
with a big party.

608
00:29:35,220 --> 00:29:36,220
Ada, Alan,

609
00:29:36,220 --> 00:29:37,220
Toni, Marie,

610
00:29:37,220 --> 00:29:38,220
Konrad,

611
00:29:38,220 --> 00:29:39,220
and other children

612
00:29:39,220 --> 00:29:40,220
from school

613
00:29:40,220 --> 00:29:41,220
and their parents,

614
00:29:41,220 --> 00:29:42,220
the president,

615
00:29:42,220 --> 00:29:43,220
Ms. Garnet,

616
00:29:43,220 --> 00:29:44,220
the bus driver,

617
00:29:44,220 --> 00:29:45,220
the custodian,

618
00:29:45,220 --> 00:29:47,220
they were all there.

619
00:29:47,220 --> 00:29:48,220
They decorated the streets,

620
00:29:48,220 --> 00:29:50,220
listened to loud music,

621
00:29:50,220 --> 00:29:51,220
and ate ice cream

622
00:29:51,220 --> 00:29:52,220
as much as they wanted.

623
00:29:52,220 --> 00:29:53,220
And in every imaginable

624
00:29:53,220 --> 00:29:55,220
shape and color.

625
00:29:55,220 --> 00:29:56,220
While the others

626
00:29:56,220 --> 00:29:57,220
continued partying

627
00:29:57,220 --> 00:29:58,220
late into the night,

628
00:29:58,220 --> 00:29:59,220
Ada and her friends

629
00:29:59,220 --> 00:30:00,220
slipped away

630
00:30:00,220 --> 00:30:01,220
to their workshop.

631
00:30:01,220 --> 00:30:02,220
They already had

632
00:30:02,220 --> 00:30:03,220
a lot of ideas

633
00:30:03,220 --> 00:30:04,220
for new inventions.

634
00:30:04,220 --> 00:30:05,220
And they wanted

635
00:30:05,220 --> 00:30:06,220
to start right away.

636
00:30:06,220 --> 00:30:07,220
And Zangemann?

637
00:30:07,220 --> 00:30:08,220
No one's heard

638
00:30:08,220 --> 00:30:09,220
much from him.

639
00:30:20,220 --> 00:30:21,220
Maybe he's still

640
00:30:21,220 --> 00:30:22,220
sitting angrily

641
00:30:22,220 --> 00:30:23,220
in front of his

642
00:30:23,220 --> 00:30:24,220
golden computer.

643
00:30:24,220 --> 00:30:28,220
Maybe he doesn't dare

644
00:30:28,220 --> 00:30:29,220
go out into the street

645
00:30:29,220 --> 00:30:30,220
anymore.

646
00:30:30,220 --> 00:30:31,220
and he has boarded up

647
00:30:31,220 --> 00:30:32,220
all the windows

648
00:30:32,220 --> 00:30:33,220
of his mansion

649
00:30:33,220 --> 00:30:34,220
so that he doesn't

650
00:30:34,220 --> 00:30:35,220
have to worry about

651
00:30:35,220 --> 00:30:36,220
what other people

652
00:30:36,220 --> 00:30:37,220
are doing

653
00:30:37,220 --> 00:30:38,220
with his inventions.

654
00:30:38,220 --> 00:30:39,220
But maybe he also

655
00:30:39,220 --> 00:30:40,220
sometimes looks out

656
00:30:40,220 --> 00:30:41,220
into the world

657
00:30:41,220 --> 00:30:42,220
through his telescope

658
00:30:42,220 --> 00:30:44,220
and sees what the children

659
00:30:44,220 --> 00:30:45,220
are inventing every day.

660
00:30:45,220 --> 00:30:48,220
Perhaps then

661
00:30:48,220 --> 00:30:49,220
he will remember

662
00:30:49,220 --> 00:30:50,220
how much fun it was

663
00:30:50,220 --> 00:30:51,220
for himself

664
00:30:51,220 --> 00:30:52,220
to tinker

665
00:30:52,220 --> 00:30:53,220
and experiment.

666
00:30:53,220 --> 00:30:56,220
And maybe,

667
00:30:56,220 --> 00:30:58,220
just maybe,

668
00:30:58,220 --> 00:30:59,220
he eats

669
00:30:59,220 --> 00:31:00,220
pyramid-shaped

670
00:31:00,220 --> 00:31:01,220
raspberry ice cream

671
00:31:01,220 --> 00:31:03,220
with rainbow sprinkles.
